    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PS110-7, PS145-7 - DISASSEMBLE - SHIFT TOWER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SHIFT TOWER</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301602">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301602" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301602" filename="../figg13/G1301602.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 2. Shift Tower Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the six retaining bolts and lockwashers. Separate the tower from the shifter housing
                and gasket. Lift straight up.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the shift lever tower on edge in a vise.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull up on the boot. Depress the spring retainer against the spring. Remove the pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the lever cover up the shift lever and remove the rock shaft snap ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tap the rock shaft free of the tower. Remove the shift lever. Remove the seal and discard
                it.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shaft lever handle and slide the boot, spring retainer, spring, and lever cover
                off the lever.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wash all parts thoroughly and inspect the lever and rock shaft cross holes for excessive
                wear. Replace all worn or damaged parts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check spring tension by comparing the old spring to a new one. Replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
